# PWA — vite-plugin-pwa

## Tooling

Use `vite-plugin-pwa` — do not hand-roll service workers unless a skill explicitly requires it.

## Manifest

- `display: standalone`
- Theme colors from project design tokens (e.g. `docs/design/tokens.md`)
- Provide maskable icons (192px, 512px)

## Offline caching

- Cache app shell and static assets.
- **Do not** cache authenticated API responses by default.

## Service worker scope

SW is for caching and installability. Core app flows must work without SW-only hooks (native Capacitor builds may differ).

## Installability

Lighthouse PWA checks are acceptance criteria for frontend changes.

## Push notifications

Access through `frontend/src/platform/notifications.ts`, not directly via browser APIs.

## Meta tags

Include `apple-mobile-web-app-capable` and `viewport-fit=cover` to align with Capacitor full-screen shell.

Adjust path globs if the frontend directory differs.
